Performing on stage in front of an audience is the greatest thing. I'm going to be sad when this is over... only four more shows. :( I can't wait until Julia and Leah see it though. I'm really glad that I'm in the theatre magnet. Phwa.

I want them to post the pics...like NOOWW.

gah/


Oh. Non-Play stuff.

I went to bed at 5 am last night, and I woke up at 2 this afternoon. I watched Moulin Rouge, and took a shower...and that's all, really.
Tonight was opening night. I got lovely letters and gifts before the show, and ACK! It was so...indescribable. I'm too excited to write anything else.
an online quiz just told me that i smell bad.

I had a lovely weekend/week. 

HAHAHAHAAA. Can you tell that I need sleep?

I couldn't show, I couldn't sleep, I was a bitch, and I got sick. And I cried a lot.

I don't feel like going into detail. 

Fuck.

oh,

Rob gave me a hug ^.^

I've been thinking alot today. Mostly about nothing. 

I <3 Cramped Fingers.


I can't write what I'm feeling, AGAIN.
I spent the weekend at my grandparents which means that I slept and read. I'm going to bed. Yes.

I haven't updated in forever...well, at least it seems that way. I've been so busy with Annie practices and shows, and blah that I haven't touched the computer. 

Did I write about 'promotion'? I hope so, because I don't feel like writing about it. Phwa.

I'm exhausted and I think I smell.

My journal is friends only now. 


I just don't want some people reading it. 

sigh.

Yesterday was the King's Island trip. It was fun, considering the fact that we were all soaked and frozen.

I rode:

Nothing much happened worth talking about, really. Neh.

I'm going to be July in Annie. Pwha!

I just realized that I haven't said much to anyone about Dave Grohl lately. I must be sick. Oh. I redid my wall last night...my giant dave poster stares at me. It's just a tad bit scary. (Current pic count:35+ on wall 100+ around house/school 550 on computer) 

I finished my Kurt tile last week. It turned out pretty good. I must take pictures. Yes.

*dies*

I got called back for Annie...mwa. Mwa. Mwa. I have to do another song this time so eh. I like my new one better anyway. (it's from The Sound Of Music x.x) 

Um. I got one hour of sleep last night. I watched silly movies. I have nothing else to say.

I know what it means to be exhausted, really truely exhausted now. I was so out of it on wednesday that I slept through most of school. I haven't been able to sleep lately, and with working on my things for the audition tomarrow, and getting ready for show season, I've just been making it worse. Euk.

Everyone at school likes my Kurt tile. It's completley black&white so far. All I have left are his eyes. OOH. 

Um. Tonight is Miss P's sleepover for all of the girls. Yay. I hope there are no cookie wars.

Today we started working on our tiles. (We paint the ceiling tiles in Miss P's class) and I didn't really get to do anything to mine. I decided to do a kurt tile, and a david grohl tile, but I can't decide how to do my david grohl one. *GAH!* I get to do two tiles this year, since the movers broke my Nirvana tile. *grrrrr* 

Um. That was pointless. Eh. Goes to show you that I'm stupid when I'm bored.

Today has been rather uneventful.  I've worked on my project for Ms. Warlop, I watched Invader Zim, and I read a chapter of the virgin suicides. For some reason I'm really hot and dizzy.

I'm going to watch the Practice tomarrow, because of Hannibal Lecter. (Though it's not Anthony, I'll live.)

One of my two best best friends HATES me. 

Why? Because she's being immature. She's "deeply insulted" because I was asked specifically to audition for Annie. She won't talk to me, she won't look at me, and she rams into my desk. I don't know whether to cry, or be angry or what. And now she's invited Ashley (who last week she hated) to come to her house and meet Dillion and buy fairy wings and eat her evil pancakes. I was invited, but she sort of...uninvited me. I'm pissed and sad. Confused. Oi.

I bought the Virgin Suicides tonight...I can't wait to read it, but I'm saving it for the weekend.

Leah is VERY mad at me. For no good reason really. She found out that Miss P's sister asked me to audition for annie, and now she's fucking pissed. (lovely language eh?) She won't even look at me, which I think is stupid and immature. And the really stupid thing is that SHE could audition if she wanted to, but she won't swallow her big fat lump of pride and DO anything. Narf.

I had a nice talk with Julia though. I gave her a letter the other day. I <3 letters. eh.

Hm. Earthlink is working again. Hmm. I have to write a speech tonight for my debate in science. I don't like writing speeches.


EEEH! The audition for Annie is next weekend, and I don't know where my monologe shit is. And I have to SING. I'm nervous. EEP.

Nothing much.

Eep! I <3 my journal's new layout. It fits my new 'even in his youth' obsession. 

I saw the Virgin Suicides today...wow. I MUST find it on video...I'm going to look for the book tomarrow, when my school goes to the big downtown creep-o library. Other than that, nothing happened today. I took notes, I got a new icon, I read some more of Heavier Than Heaven, and I ate some nachos. Yum.

-Take notes from Please Kill Me
-Work on new layout and content on my retarted little site

-E-mail people
-Disconnect cordless phone

Ok...I think that's all...

Random:I <3 Even In His Youth. I even have even in his youth wallpaper. Oi.

I've been taken over by a lethargic slug, which has given me intense chest pains, the only thing that bothered me today as I laid in bed...or wherever. I'm so tired, but I can't sleep. And I forgot to buy cup of soup last night, so I have no hot noodle-y broth to soothe my chest pains. I sound like an old women who has smoked all of her life. Speaking of old women, I saw the Tenacious D video "Tribute" today. I think I'm going to download it. Yes.

I just lied to my Grandma. Can I go to prison for that?

<3<3<3 We Got the Neutron Bomb

I had an ok day today. 

Nothing special happened at school. We did get a new fridge which makes me happy. Cold food!!! *dies*

Um. I don't feel like I'm being very honest with myself.



Grr. Sid And Nancy is on tonight. I'd like to watch, but mom is home...eh. I get to see the Virgin Suicides this weekend. Yay.

I feel odd. Kind of dizzy, but mostly like I'm stuck in a bubble. A big bubble that I can see out of. Purple. Maybe the bubble has cotton in it to muffle my senses and make me feel trapped. Everything feels weird.

I don't feel like writing.

I got my graduation dress. I think that it's kind of silly to dress up for eighth grade graduation, but I'll do it even if it's just because Leah is forcing me too. 

I <3 my new chuck taylor's. I got Gir shoestrings for them. Mwa.
Eh. I want to find nice quotes. Grr.

I've felt sick all day. I don't know why. I'm still freaked about Skeeter.
I.i.I.i. 
Judy gave me a sketchbook/diary set thing, but I can't use it, because I've had some sort of fucking block. I can't draw anything anymore except for people with metal parts. I've hardly used my new sketchbook. 
I'm going to be sick.

We had a field trip to the creek today. We've gone 4 times, but I've only made it once. I never want to go again. I'm covered in little red itchy bumps...that are itchy. And some parent (and trish the leader) told me to put antibacterial stuff on it, and that only made it burn. 

I'm going to the barn this weekend. Yay. I get to babysit, and I want to see about running for secretary of the youth team. Yesh.

I gave Skeeter a rice crispie treat. I'm being nice. That's my job. Woo. 

Oh. Today was art, and I painted my paper mache ovary/oviduct. I also painted my arm with pretty colors and hole lyrics because I was bored. Mr. Utley thinks I'm odd. Go me.

My hair is shitscumevilmedusa hair. It's everywhere and it won't lay down. 

Things that I liked about today:
Rob was nice. 
I did well in my classes.
It was a half day at school.

Things that I didn't like about today:
I just jammed a straw into my forehead. 
Courtney pissed me off.
Alicia spoiled my fun.
Noah almost blew away.
Why do I still have nightmares/dreams about him?

Ok. Opening a book to the chapter that you need to take notes on for Miss Warlop's class, and finding Sid Vicious with his pants dropped is...not a very good thing. Yesh. My mom is yelling about pots, and being very annnoying. I went to the library. I managed to find a few good books and a Dinosaur Jr cd, so...eh that was good. 

Leah wants to set me up with her friend Dillion. I hate boys. Blech. Well...I hate the boys that I know. They're grr. Yes, they are grr. That's the only *nice* word that I can think of right now.

Today was just boring. I read, I chose a topic for a research paper, I took a test, I cut out pictures of shamrocks, and I fell down the stairs. Oh and I stayed at the barn until 10:00. That's it. Blah.

Eh. Today was...not fun? I got to skip social studies though, so that was fairly fun. Other than that I've had cramps (because i forgot to take my medicine)and now my back hurts because I fell off of the couch and I also got dragged along the floor in my living room. Ow. 

Um. I wore shorts today, and since I NEVER wear shorts, I'm begining to think that that is why I've had such a um...day. Um. I drew labels on some cds that mark burned for me last night. Oh. And I got an invader zim hoodie and patch. I'm so special. Oh. And I got tons of new tack. Yeah. Ace was an asshole. For the first time too. Grr.

I felt odd all day. I just felt so...alien, like I didn't really belong anywhere. I used to feel like that a lot, and it's not a very pleasent feeling. Of course back then, I actually was being alienated against (stupid fucks...thought I was some sort of dirty whore. I hate rumors. And lies, and boys with red hair.) and now I'm not, but still...

Miss Bastine is going to drive me insane. She made me remove staples. The last time I removed staples in her room, I ended up going to the doctor, with metal in my eye. Um.

Mark burned Adore and Screaming Fields of Sonic Love for me. Yay. I want to order a shirt from Sonicyouth.com...yes.

School starts tomarrow. I want to hide in bed, and not go to school. I don't want to see those people any more. The good thing is that I only have to see them for about 7 more weeks. Yay. Seven weeks to go. Then summer. Then high school. Ummm...I need to ask Miss P when the audtions for Annie are. I think that they're in May, or late April but I'm not sure. Her sister wants me to audition. Woo. Um. I saw Richard today, but just for a few minutes. Yeah. I need to read my chapter in math, but eh..fuck it.

I went back to the horse fair today, and as I was walking in Katie came up to me and dragged me to the maba booth because Richard was there!! He almost threw me when he spun me around, and um.....I saw too many people that I know today. 
That's ok though, because I got to see Richard, and I missed Richard and GAH! He's coming back tomarrow. Yay. Um. I haven't really felt like writing much this week. I've been too tired most of the time. Eh. 

Ummm...I watched Nirvana videos last night. And um..

Leah called tonight. She's  been writing all day, and she wrote a poem about me. (That's a scary thing. Me??) And umm....it was really nice. I'll post it here when she gived me a copy of it next week at school. Gah. I don't even want to think about school.

I finished We Got The Neutron Bomb last night, it was really good. I'll read it again next week during miss warlop's classes. Yay.

Ummm. I've been going to the barn this week. Ace is doing so well. Meek. Ummmmm. I slept in today, and I still have a nasty cold. I watched Alexis for a while yesterday, and I finally bought Bleach.Ummm. Tomarrow I get to go visit the Amish man, and Friday is the hoosier horse fair, which means shopping, shopping shopping. Woo.
I woke up earlier today than I do on school days. Um. I went to the barn, and nothing much happened. Yesh.

My mom gave me a little lavender bunny for Easter, since she wouldn't be home. She's kind of upset because Easter was always really special to her when she was little. She wants it to be special for me to, and I guess that's a nice thought, but she doesn't seem to remember that my last two Easters were at a horse show in Kentucky and umm...at my grandparents. Um. Nothing much has happened. Yah.
I voice chatted with Trey, who is a poo, with an adorable voice. I'm going to bottle it. I, on the other hand have a nasty voice. I know. I'm dumb. Poof.
